\subsection*{Prophage induction - planned work}
Methods from \citep{rubin_dietary_2019}. Bacteria were cultured in the presence of each of the test compounds for 24 h in 96-well plates. A single colony from each isolate was used to inoculate a 3 mL liquid overnight culture, and 140 Î¼L of diluted overnight culture (1:10 in media) was then mixed with 10 Î¼L of test compound solution. For isolates requiring anaerobic conditions, volumes were doubled and 96-well plates sealed with film to promote anaerobic conditions. The following controls were included: media alone (media control), bacteria in media without test compound (bacterial viability control), and each diluent used for the various test compounds. Using a Varioskan plate reader/incubator, optical density (OD) at 600 nm (OD600 nm) was measured every 10 min. Each test was accompanied by a positive âinductionâ control of carbadox (Sigma-Aldrich) at a range of final concentrations.

